The house of bones fascinates even after 100 years. Look at the interiors from Gaudí
The roof looks like the back of an ancient pond, the staircase resembles the spine of a dinosaur and the balconies are open fish mouth.
This is the house of Casa Batlló in Barcelona by the Catalan architect Antoni Gaudí.
From the local house thanks to its organic shapes he earned the nickname House from bones.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stone, fragments of tiles and mosaics, a facade reminiscent of skulls and ubiquitous soft curves, all of which are typical for the secession of Antoni Gaudí.
