The Ecological Europe-Greens Association (EE-LV) has proposed to establish a moratorium on the use of pesticides to stop “the rise of civilizational diseases”.
In July, the European Food Safety Agency (EFSA) examined the status of residues of 365 different pesticides identified in fruit and vegetables consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
